Days spent on PHC clinical and normal daily administrative work related to client care, are counted. One actual work day is normally equivalent to an 8-hour shift (40 hours). Professional nurses can be full time or part time employed. Work day equivalents:
2 hours or less = 0.25 clinical work day;
3-4 hours = 0.5 clinical work day;
5-6 hours = 0.75 work day;
7-8 hours = 1 clinical work day;
12 hour shift = 1.5 work days;
The clinical work days put in by each Professional nurse must be added up.

